cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a novel hierarchical computation architecture that involves edge computing to improve the performance of mobile AR applications. This involves networking and internet architecture, making cs.NI the most likely category.
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the components of general AR applications and fashionable AR devices, which are related to multimedia. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses existing techniques for overcoming latency and energy consumption problems in AR applications, which are related to computer vision and pattern recognition.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed architecture involves distributed computing between the user layer, edge layer, and cloud layer, making cs.DC a likely category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an innovated operation mechanism to improve the performance of mobile AR applications, which involves control systems.
